story.title: Ensnare - Episode 2
story.storyDescription: The President’s 17-year-old daughter has just discovered she’s pregnant…but she’s not the only one with a secret.
story.creator: web-uploader

author.bio: Chelsea Bobulski is the author of the YA contemporary fantasy The Wood. She loves to write about characters with broken pasts, strange talents, and obstacles they must overcome for a brighter future.

story.prePaywallNotification: What?! Angie wants to keep the baby? Tap back into Hooked to see how her boyfriend Kyle will respond 😬👶
story.postPaywallNotification: Poor Angie! Sounds like her father’s presidency puts a lot of responsibility on her shoulders. Tap back into Hooked to see if it makes her crack 😬💔

messages.text: So, what will you do if you have the baby?
How will you take care of it?
I don’t know — I haven’t thought that far out yet.
Honestly, I don’t even know if I *actually* want to keep it.
But for once, I just want to feel like I have a choice.
Of course you have a choice, Angie.
Is there something else I should know?
Cameras flash. Angie smiles to the parade crowd.
No. I’m just a little freaked out.
At 2 a.m., after the Inauguration is over, Angie gets another text from Will.
Or are you at some fancy party? 😝
Haha, just got back from the last fancy party.
This is supposed to be our house, but it feels like I’m staying at a hotel.
Massive. I have this huge four-poster bed.
Mom put up these antique-y drapes around my balcony. It overlooks the garden.
Did she at least let you put up your Ruth Bader Ginsburg poster?
Yeah, but I had to compromise…
So now it’s in this huge frame that supposedly belonged to Thomas Jefferson.
Why’d you stop talking to me?
Classes, work…it was hard to keep up.
Well, at least we’re talking now.
You have a human growing inside of you.
Have you ever thought about it?
What you would do if you got someone pregnant?
It wouldn’t really be my choice, would it?
What if she wanted to keep it?
Not that I’ve had the opportunity to make this a possibility, but…
I’d support the kid the best I could. He’d be my responsibility too.
Why? Does the father want you to get rid of it?
Or do you think he won’t help support it?
This choice affects a lot more people than just me and the father.
What will people say about him when they find out I’m knocked up?
His approval ratings are going to tank, and it’ll be because of something *I* did.
Angie…you can’t take on all of that responsibility.
Your dad chose to be the president.
He knows people are going to talk about him.
YOU get to choose whether you have this baby or not.
You guess? What does that mean?
Fine, you don’t have to tell me, but please, keep talking to me.
Tell me more about your room.
What other horrible decorations did your mom put up? 🙈
Um…there’s a giant metal peacock by the fireplace?
See, I always suspected the White House had a giant metal peacock problem.
But I didn’t really believe it until just now.
Still hacking into the school’s computer system for fun?
Only when people pay me to change their grades.
Says she’s gonna stay clean this time.
She doesn’t exactly have the best track record.
If I say yes, will you deliver it to Cali personally? 😉
But seriously, are you guys okay?
You wouldn’t believe the number of trust fund kids failing their classes.
They keep food on the table.
If it helps, I’m much better now that I’m talking to you.
Angie’s phone dings with a new text from Kyle. Angie switches over to her text chain with him.
I spoke to the Source again.
They want to officially invite you to become a member.
They’re guaranteeing to make all of your dreams come true.
But we can’t keep the baby.
The abortion’s been scheduled for next Friday.
